observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Treasurer to:

stringently require the submission of the Copy of the Certified ITR from all the taxpayers pursuant to Section 2E.04(e) of the Municipal Revenue Code of 2017 to guarantee that the basis in the computation of business taxes is correct;

Thereafter, verify, assess and compare the gross sales or receipts considered in the computation of business taxes and in the ITR; and collect penalties and surcharges, if any.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:

Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with a complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;


Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant to determine or, if not practicable, estimate the carrying amount of the assets replaced taking into consideration the cost, age and condition of the replaced asset;

Thereafter, Municipal Accountant to make necessary adjustments in the Local Road Networks account for the derecognition of the replaced assets; and


Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain subsidiary ledgers for each component, containing distinctive information such as measurement of the project component to facilitate in future derecognition of assets in the book of accounts as a result of rehabilitation or improvements made.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct:

The General Services Officer to prepare and maintain the required Property Cards; 


Thereafter, provide the necessary data to the Municipal Engineer and GSO in the conduct of physical inventory of local roads;

Provide depreciation expense for each of the component;


Provide disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements for Local Road Network;


The General Services Officer to prepare and maintain the required Local Road Networks Property Card and include in the conduct of inventory the Local Road Networks;

The General Services Officer to prepare and submit Local Road Inventory and Road Map.

We recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to:
coordinate with the appropriate offices to strategically assign tasks and responsibilities among personnel to strengthen internal control, improve the accuracy and efficiency of financial reporting and expedite the reconciliation of remittances to the appropriate government agencies;
ensure the timely updating and reconciliation of employee records with GSIS, Pag-IBIG, and PhilHealth to facilitate the accurate remittance and proper settlement of outstanding balances from prior years;
review the monthly premiums deducted from payroll/DVs for GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth, to ensure that the amounts withheld match the amounts due for remittance each month; and
strictly comply with the provisions of RA No. 8291, RA No. 9769 and Revised IRR of RA No. 7875, to avoid administrative sanctions and ensure proper fulfillment of the Municipality’s obligations to the concerned agencies.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
The General Services Officer to prepare and maintain the required Property Cards




The Inventory Committee to conduct inventory and use the updated records of the GSO and Municipal Accountant to facilitate conduct of inventory and preparation of report;




The Municipal Accountant to trace and duly account local road network transactions prior to CY 2018 through journals, disbursement vouchers, supporting documents and other reports.

Thereafter, provide the necessary data to the Municipal Engineer and GSO in the conduct of physical inventory of local roads;




Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components based on the data to be provided by the Municipal Engineer for every road network; 




Provide depreciation expense for each of the component;




Provide disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements for Local Road Network;

The General Services Officer to prepare and maintain the required Local Road Networks Property Card and include in the conduct of inventory the Local Road Networks;

The General Services Officer to prepare and submit Local Road Inventory and Road Map; and

The Municipal Engineer to provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects

We have recommended that the Management:

Ensure that the buildings and other properties be insured with the GSIS;


Determine the fair market value of the buildings with the assistance of the Municipal Engineer and Assessor;



Include appropriations for premiums for the properties mentioned above;

Determine the book value of the buildings with the assistance of the Municipal Accountant and the Inventory Committee; and


Complete all the necessary requirements needed for the application of property insurance.

