We recommended and the Municipal Mayor committed to direct the:
Inventory Committee to convene and plan the inventory taking and submit the required reports;
Municipal Accountant to:
maintain Property, Plant and Equipment ledger cards (PPELCs) and Real Property Ledger Cards (RPLC) instead of lists of PPE acquisitions and to trace the details of prior years’ acquisitions of Property, Plant and Equipment by category in order to complete the property ledger cards;
prepare adjusting entries for provision for impairment for unserviceable properties;
prepare lapsing schedules for all depreciable assets to support the provision for depreciation; and
prepare necessary entry to take-up donated properties.
GSO – Designate to maintain property cards with complete details and reconcile the same with accounting records and Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment and further inquire or verify the reasons for discrepancies and recommend necessary management action;
Disposal Committee to check the unserviceable properties and recommend necessary management action.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor committed to enjoin the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System.  Further, to direct the:
Municipal Accountant to:
Maintain the subsidiary ledgers for every component of Road Network;
Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements on the total road network system of the Municipality; and
Trace prior years’ records/documents pertaining to road network and record the same to properly account the Road Network;
GSO-Designate to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;
Municipal Engineer to provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
The Inventory Committee to prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System of the local government unit.

We reiterated and the Local Chief Executive positively agreed to instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
Further look into previous years’ files or documents in order to account for the said receivables;
Confirm thereafter if the debtors were already identified;
Require for the liquidation of the said receivable and verify the propriety of the submitted documents, and prepare the necessary adjusting entries; and
If after all the possible means were exerted and the claims could not be accounted, request for write-off of the above receivables supported by above cited documents.

We have recommended and the Local Chief Executive committed to direct the:
Accountable Officers to return to the GSO Designate the unserviceable properties;
GSO Designate to:
cancel the ARE related to the unserviceable properties turned-over to him;
initiate the disposal in accordance with the requirements provided in COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992 and Section 79 of PD No. 1445 to avoid further deterioration due to natural elements and possible loss due to theft and loss of value, generate additional funds, if found valuable and sold.

The Local Chief Executive to create inventory committee to conduct physical inventory of all Property, Plant and Equipment of the municipality in order to determine their existence and condition;

The GSO to maintain property cards per category of PPE;

The Accounting unit to maintain complete property ledger cards for all PPE owned by the agency;


Additionally:
The GSO Designate to issue ARE to all property accountable officials and employees and keep copies thereof;



The GSO designate and Accounting unit to exert effort in reconciling their records;

f.	 The GSO designate and Accounting unit to effect the proper documentation and immediate disposition of all unserviceable property.

The Accounting unit to exert effort in locating or producing the documents to support the legitimacy of the unreconciled PPE account balances and hereafter, strengthen the control over documentation of all financial transactions.


h. The Accounting unit to disclose in their notes the change in accounting estimate due to decrease in residual value and the gross carrying amount of any fully depreciated property, plant and equipment that is still in use.
